    <div class="header">
        <h1>-ING Forms Classification</h1>
        <div class="subtitle">Identify whether each highlighted -ING form functions as a noun, adjective, verb, or adverb</div>
    </div>

    <div class="instructions">
        <h3>Quick Reference Guide</h3>
        <div class="category-guide">
            <div class="category-card noun">
                <h4>As a NOUN (Gerund)</h4>
                <p><strong>Swimming</strong> is fun<br>
                I enjoy <strong>reading</strong><br>
                After <strong>studying</strong>...</p>
            </div>
            <div class="category-card adjective">
                <h4>As an ADJECTIVE (Participle)</h4>
                <p>An <strong>exciting</strong> match<br>
                The book is <strong>boring</strong><br>
                A man <strong>standing</strong> there</p>
            </div>
            <div class="category-card verb">
                <h4>As a VERB (Continuous)</h4>
                <p>I am <strong>studying</strong><br>
                She was <strong>reading</strong><br>
                They are <strong>playing</strong></p>
            </div>
            <div class="category-card adverb">
                <h4>As an ADVERB (Participle)</h4>
                <p><strong>Walking</strong> home, I...<br>
                <strong>Being</strong> tired, she...<br>
                He left, <strong>feeling</strong> sad</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="exercise">
        <h2>Classification Exercise</h2>
        <p>Choose the correct function for each highlighted -ING form:</p>

        <div class="sentence">
            <div class="sentence-number">1</div>
            <p><span class="highlight">Swimming</span> is very good for your health.</p>
            <div class="options">
                <div class="option" data-answer="noun">Noun</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adjective">Adjective</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="verb">Verb</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adverb">Adverb</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feedback">
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> "Swimming" is the subject of the sentence, functioning as a noun.</p>
                <p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> "Swimming" is the subject of the sentence, so it functions as a noun.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sentence">
            <div class="sentence-number">2</div>
            <p>That programme was really <span class="highlight">boring</span>.</p>
            <div class="options">
                <div class="option" data-answer="noun">Noun</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adjective">Adjective</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="verb">Verb</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adverb">Adverb</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feedback">
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> "Boring" describes the programme, functioning as an adjective after the linking verb "was".</p>
                <p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> "Boring" describes the programme, so it functions as an adjective after the linking verb "was".</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sentence">
            <div class="sentence-number">3</div>
            <p>I am currently <span class="highlight">learning</span> French at university.</p>
            <div class="options">
                <div class="option" data-answer="noun">Noun</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adjective">Adjective</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="verb">Verb</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adverb">Adverb</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feedback">
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> "Learning" is part of the present continuous tense "am learning", functioning as a verb.</p>
                <p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> "Learning" is part of the present continuous tense "am learning", so it functions as a verb.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sentence">
            <div class="sentence-number">4</div>
            <p>We enjoy <span class="highlight">studying</span> English grammar.</p>
            <div class="options">
                <div class="option" data-answer="noun">Noun</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adjective">Adjective</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="verb">Verb</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adverb">Adverb</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feedback">
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> "Studying" is the object of the verb "enjoy", functioning as a noun.</p>
                <p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> "Studying" is the object of the verb "enjoy", so it functions as a noun.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sentence">
            <div class="sentence-number">5</div>
            <p><span class="highlight">Walking</span> to campus, I met my friend from high school.</p>
            <div class="options">
                <div class="option" data-answer="noun">Noun</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adjective">Adjective</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="verb">Verb</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adverb">Adverb</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feedback">
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> "Walking to campus" modifies the main clause, explaining when/how the meeting happened, functioning as an adverb.</p>
                <p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> "Walking to campus" modifies the main clause, explaining when/how the meeting happened, so it functions as an adverb.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sentence">
            <div class="sentence-number">6</div>
            <p>The most <span class="highlight">challenging</span> part of LEA studies is business terminology.</p>
            <div class="options">
                <div class="option" data-answer="noun">Noun</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adjective">Adjective</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="verb">Verb</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adverb">Adverb</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feedback">
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> "Challenging" modifies the noun "part", functioning as an adjective.</p>
                <p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> "Challenging" modifies the noun "part", so it functions as an adjective.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sentence">
            <div class="sentence-number">7</div>
            <p>I heard someone <span class="highlight">playing</span> the piano in the music room.</p>
            <div class="options">
                <div class="option" data-answer="noun">Noun</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adjective">Adjective</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="verb">Verb</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adverb">Adverb</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feedback">
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> "Playing" describes the ongoing action after a verb of perception, functioning as a verb.</p>
                <p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> "Playing" describes the ongoing action after a verb of perception, so it functions as a verb.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sentence">
            <div class="sentence-number">8</div>
            <p>Some people are not interested in <span class="highlight">learning</span> foreign languages.</p>
            <div class="options">
                <div class="option" data-answer="noun">Noun</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adjective">Adjective</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="verb">Verb</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adverb">Adverb</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feedback">
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> "Learning" follows the preposition "in", functioning as a noun (gerund).</p>
                <p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> "Learning" follows the preposition "in", so it functions as a noun (gerund).</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sentence">
            <div class="sentence-number">9</div>
            <p><span class="highlight">Being</span> a first-year student, she finds university life quite different from high school.</p>
            <div class="options">
                <div class="option" data-answer="noun">Noun</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adjective">Adjective</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="verb">Verb</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adverb">Adverb</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feedback">
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> "Being a first-year student" gives the reason for the main statement, functioning as an adverb.</p>
                <p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> "Being a first-year student" gives the reason for the main statement, so it functions as an adverb.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="sentence">
            <div class="sentence-number">10</div>
            <p>The students were <span class="highlight">discussing</span> their Erasmus application plans.</p>
            <div class="options">
                <div class="option" data-answer="noun">Noun</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adjective">Adjective</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="verb">Verb</div>
                <div class="option" data-answer="adverb">Adverb</div>
            </div>
            <div class="feedback">
                <p><strong>Correct!</strong> "Discussing" is part of the past continuous tense "were discussing", functioning as a verb.</p>
                <p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> "Discussing" is part of the past continuous tense "were discussing", so it functions as a verb.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="controls">
            <button class="check-btn" onclick="checkAnswers()">Check All Answers</button>
            <button class="reset-btn" onclick="resetExercise()">Reset Exercise</button>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="results" id="results">
        <h2>Exercise Results</h2>
        <div class="score" id="score">0/10</div>
        <p id="feedback-message"></p>
    </div>

    <script>
        const correctAnswers = {
            1: 'noun',      // Swimming is very good for your health
            2: 'adjective', // That programme was really boring
            3: 'verb',      // I am currently learning French
            4: 'noun',      // We enjoy studying English grammar
            5: 'adverb',    // Walking to campus, I met my friend
            6: 'adjective', // The most challenging part
            7: 'verb',      // I heard someone playing the piano
            8: 'noun',      // interested in learning foreign languages
            9: 'adverb',    // Being a first-year student
            10: 'verb'      // The students were discussing
        };

        let userAnswers = {};

        // Handle option selection
        document.querySelectorAll('.option').forEach(option => {
            option.addEventListener('click', function() {
                const sentence = this.closest('.sentence');
                const sentenceNum = Array.from(sentence.parentElement.children).indexOf(sentence) + 1;
                const options = sentence.querySelectorAll('.option');
                
                // Remove previous selection
                options.forEach(opt => opt.classList.remove('selected'));
                
                // Select current option
                this.classList.add('selected');
                
                // Store user answer
                userAnswers[sentenceNum] = this.dataset.answer;
            });
        });

        function checkAnswers() {
            let score = 0;
            const totalQuestions = Object.keys(correctAnswers).length;

            Object.keys(correctAnswers).forEach(questionNum => {
                const sentence = document.querySelectorAll('.sentence')[questionNum - 1];
                const options = sentence.querySelectorAll('.option');
                const feedback = sentence.querySelector('.feedback');
                const userAnswer = userAnswers[questionNum];
                const correctAnswer = correctAnswers[questionNum];

                // Reset option styles
                options.forEach(opt => {
                    opt.classList.remove('correct', 'incorrect');
                });

                if (userAnswer) {
                    if (userAnswer === correctAnswer) {
                        score++;
                        // Mark correct answer
                        options.forEach(opt => {
                            if (opt.dataset.answer === correctAnswer) {
                                opt.classList.add('correct');
                            }
                        });
                        feedback.className = 'feedback show correct';
                        feedback.innerHTML = feedback.children[0].innerHTML;
                    } else {
                        // Mark incorrect answer and show correct one
                        options.forEach(opt => {
                            if (opt.dataset.answer === userAnswer) {
                                opt.classList.add('incorrect');
                            } else if (opt.dataset.answer === correctAnswer) {
                                opt.classList.add('correct');
                            }
                        });
                        feedback.className = 'feedback show incorrect';
                        feedback.innerHTML = feedback.children[1].innerHTML;
                    }
                } else {
                    // Show correct answer for unanswered questions
                    options.forEach(opt => {
                        if (opt.dataset.answer === correctAnswer) {
                            opt.classList.add('correct');
                        }
                    });
                    feedback.className = 'feedback show incorrect';
                    feedback.innerHTML = '<p><strong>No answer selected.</strong> ' + feedback.children[1].innerHTML.replace('<p><strong>Incorrect.</strong> ', '') + '</p>';
                }
            });

            // Show results
            const resultsDiv = document.getElementById('results');
            const scoreDiv = document.getElementById('score');
            const feedbackMessage = document.getElementById('feedback-message');

            scoreDiv.textContent = `${score}/${totalQuestions}`;
            
            if (score === totalQuestions) {
                feedbackMessage.innerHTML = 'Perfect! You have excellent understanding of -ING forms!';
            } else if (score >= totalQuestions * 0.8) {
                feedbackMessage.innerHTML = 'Great job! You have a strong grasp of -ING forms.';
            } else if (score >= totalQuestions * 0.6) {
                feedbackMessage.innerHTML = 'Good work! Review the incorrect answers to improve your understanding.';
            } else {
                feedbackMessage.innerHTML = 'Keep studying! Review the reference guide and try again.';
            }

            resultsDiv.style.display = 'block';
            resultsDiv.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
        }

        function resetExercise() {
            // Clear user answers
            userAnswers = {};

            // Reset all options
            document.querySelectorAll('.option').forEach(option => {
                option.classList.remove('selected', 'correct', 'incorrect');
            });

            // Hide all feedback
            document.querySelectorAll('.feedback').forEach(feedback => {
                feedback.classList.remove('show');
            });

            // Hide results
            document.getElementById('results').style.display = 'none';

            // Scroll to top
            window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
